# Current Task

## Title

Review and revise the AI execution documentation.

## Objective

Review all AI documentation under the `.AI` directory and identify documentation that assumes the current `currentTask.md` execution model.

Revise the documentation to support a future queue-driven execution architecture while maintaining compatibility with the current implementation.

The repository currently uses:

- `.AI\Prompt\currentTask.md`

as the execution entry point.

Do not change this workflow.

Instead, revise the documentation so it describes:

- the current implementation
- its limitations
- a recommended evolution toward a queue-based execution model

## Current Workflow Constraint

This task must be executed using the existing workflow.

Codex should assume that `.AI\Prompt\currentTask.md` is still the active task handoff file. The new queue structure does not exist yet and must not be treated as implemented.

## Review Goals

Identify documentation that assumes:

- only one current task exists
- prompts are stored exclusively in `currentTask.md`
- all execution begins from `currentTask.md`
- ad hoc prompts must explicitly override the current task
- to-do items, diagnostics, and tasks cannot carry their own execution prompts

Recommend improvements that separate:

- Queue Items
- Prompts
- Current Task
- Run Control
- Execution History
- Ad Hoc Execution

without requiring immediate implementation.

## Future Architecture To Document

Document the proposed future structure as a recommended architecture, not as the current implementation.

Preferred future structure:

```text
.AI/
├── Prompt/
│   ├── currentTask.md
│   ├── currentTask.clear.md
│   └── ...
├── Queue/
│   ├── currentItem.json
│   ├── Todo/
│   │   ├── ready.jsonl
│   │   ├── open.jsonl
│   │   └── completed.jsonl
│   ├── Diagnostic/
│   │   ├── ready.jsonl
│   │   ├── skipped.jsonl
│   │   └── completed.jsonl
│   └── Task/
│       ├── ready.jsonl
│       ├── open.jsonl
│       └── completed.jsonl
└── RunControl/
    └── mode.json
```

## Future Design Principles To Capture

The revised documentation should describe these principles:

- Queue items represent work objects.
- A to-do item should include a concise execution prompt so Codex does not need to ask the user what to do.
- Queue items may also reference reusable named prompts or procedures.
- Reusable prompts are assets, not necessarily current tasks.
- `currentTask.md` is a temporary execution handoff file.
- In the current implementation, `currentTask.md` remains the entry point.
- In the future implementation, `currentTask.md` should be generated from the selected queue item and its associated prompt/procedure.
- Ad hoc requests should bypass queue mode.
- Clearing the current task should return the system to ad hoc mode so Codex does not keep following stale task instructions.
- Diagnostics, to-do items, project tasks, research items, and future graph-based work objects should be able to enter queues.

## Deliverables

Produce revised documentation and recommendations.

At minimum:

- Update relevant `.AI` documentation to distinguish the current workflow from the proposed future queue-driven workflow.
- Add or update examples showing how a to-do item can carry a concise execution prompt.
- Add or update examples showing how a queue item can reference a named reusable prompt.
- Document the need for clearing `currentTask.md` when switching to ad hoc mode.
- Identify obsolete or misleading documentation.
- Report any architectural inconsistencies discovered during review.

## Constraints

- Do not restructure the repository.
- Do not rename files.
- Do not create the future queue folder structure unless explicitly instructed later.
- Preserve existing terminology where practical.
- Prefer additive documentation changes.
- Preserve comments.
- Maintain Markdown formatting standards.
- Use `-` for unordered lists.
- Ensure every heading in a document is unique.
- Ensure horizontal rules are preceded by a blank line.
- Avoid unrelated formatting changes.

## Expected Codex Behavior

Codex should:

- Inspect the relevant `.AI` documentation before editing.
- Summarize the affected files before making changes.
- Make minimal documentation changes needed to align the docs with this task.
- Keep a detailed record of inspected files, commands, edits, and reasoning in the appropriate AI execution log location if such a location already exists.
- If no execution log location is documented, report that gap as a documentation issue instead of inventing a new structure.

## Completion Criteria

The task is complete when the AI documentation clearly distinguishes:

- the existing `currentTask.md` workflow
- the problem of stale current-task state during ad hoc work
- the proposed future queue-driven model
- the role of concise per-item prompts
- the role of reusable named prompts
- the role of `currentTask.md` as a runtime handoff rather than the permanent source of work
